reviews.text: Very friendly and quick service!! Great pizza and salad
I‚Äôve ate PJs Pizza since I was a little girl. It‚Äôs great to move back & have whenever I want.

The worst pizza I have ever had! The cheese wasn't melted thoroughly let alone browned and the crust was tough and  chewy on the bottom and like a biscuit in the middle. I ordered an XL with 3X cheese and 3 toppings. It was almost $27 AFTER a $5 coupon for first time order online. It could POSSIBLY be DECENT at best if it was baked correctly. NEVER going back though! detailedReviews.author: Brian Jobes
detailedReviews.text: Ordered online thru pj's website @2:40 pm to pick pizza up at 5:40 pm. Went to pick up and pizza hadnt even been made yet.... Was told they seen where i ordered it and at what time... And was told it was not made or ready because "they have other customers". Not quite sure i understand that logic. Then somehow it got onto the subject of a discount.... Nobody wants a dicount!!!!!...I want to receive the service that you took my money for. If you do not understand how to have an order ready by a certain time with advanced notice... Then do not offer that option at online check out. Word of advice... If management would ever read this.... There are a lot of pizza places out there...PJ's pizza is not the only place in town. I ordered the way i did for convenience... After all was said and done it became a big inconvenience... I don't need that..Thus i will be considering my pizza dining at other establishments.

detailedReviews.author: Christy Jobes
detailedReviews.text: Placed order online with a future pickup time. Arrived about five minutes early if pickup time, was notified my order had not been started on yet. After waiting about 12mins I went back in and was told my order was just out in the oven, I expressed that was the reason we had placed the order online for a future pickup time, so we would NOT have to wait, the young man working rudely told me that there were orders ahead of mine and that it was what it was, then preceded to tell me he would have given me 50%off but I used door dash to order instead of using the website. We dont even have the door dash app. My husband went back in to pickup our order. Do better PJ's, take a tip from your sign I front of your store...Life is too short to have bad employees who don't know how to treat customers.

detailedReviews.author: Christine Tippins
detailedReviews.text: I ordered takeout for the 2 days I was in town. To my surprise, they had gluten-free pizza and my huband had their philly cheese sub (and loved it!). The guy that answered the phone when I called in my order was knowledgeable and asked if it was an allergy, and I told him yes. I also ordered it without cheese, and without making me feel weird, he said Ok and within 20 mins, my pizza was done and delicious.  I did order ranch on the side, and I think they homemade it because it was pretty watery looking but I tried it and it was delicious as well. I was really worried at first about ordering from here because it doesn't look super appealing but don't judge a book by its cover. This place is a must try! I will be visiting again next time I'm in town.
